      "content": "You are correct that labeling wind energy as entirely \"green\" can be an oversimplification when materials and end-of-life waste are considered. Blade disposal, especially, presents a growing waste management challenge due to their composite materials. However, within the context of climate change mitigation, wind energy is still vastly superior to fossil fuels because its operational carbon footprint is near zero. The key is recognizing that \"cleaner\" doesn't mean \"zero impact,\" but it means drastically lower impact compared to combustion sources.",
